# IMAGE QUALITY SETTING (Still Photography)

## Editing Custom Settings

Edit existing custom settings banks.

1. **Select** !Image Quality Setting Icon **IMAGE QUALITY SETTING** > !Edit/Save Custom Setting Icon **EDIT/SAVE CUSTOM SETTING** in the shooting menu and press **MENU/OK**.

   > ðŸ’¡ **Note:**  
   > To save settings for movie recording, navigate to !Movie Setting Icon **MOVIE SETTING** in the movie menus and select !Edit/Save Custom Setting Icon **EDIT/SAVE CUSTOM SETTING**.

2. **Highlight** the desired custom settings bank and press **MENU/OK**.

   !Custom Settings Bank

3. **Highlight** EDIT/CHECK and press **MENU/OK**.

   !Edit/Check Menu

4. The camera will display a list of shooting menu items; highlight an item you wish to edit and press **MENU/OK**. Adjust the selected item as desired.

   !Shooting Menu Items

5. Press **MENU/OK** to save the changes and return to the shooting menu list. Adjust additional items as desired.
